Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @chicken stock powder{1/2} and @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the #pan{}. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, grated using a coarse grater) (no need to peel!) and grate using a #coarse grater{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1/2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @spring onion{1}(trimmed, thinly sliced). Trim the @green beans{150%g}(trimmed, chopped into thirds) and chop into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated using a garlic press) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved lengthways) lengthways.

== Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix the @tomato ketchup{1} with the @soy sauce{12.5%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%ml} and half the lime zest. Squeeze in half the lime juice. Chop the remaining lime into wedges.

== Toasted Coconut ==

Heat a #frying pan{} (or #wok{}) over medium high heat (no oil). Add the @desiccated coconut{12.5%g} and cook, stirring and shaking the pan frequently until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Be careful the coconut will burn easily so watch it like a hawk.

When ready, transfer to a small bowl and wipe the pan clean.

> Be careful the pan will be hot! Time to stir-fry!

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a splash of oil in your frying pan over high heat. When hot, stir-fry the @diced chicken breast{260%g} until browned on the outside, ~{5%minutes}. Add the pepper and green beans, stir-fry for another ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the carrot and garlic and cook until the veggies are tender, another ~{3-4%minutes}. Pour in the sauce and cook until bubbling, then remove immediately from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{}, stir through the remaining lime zest and share between your bowls. Top with the stir-fry and finish with a sprinkling of toasted coconut and spring onion. Serve with lime wedges on the side. Enjoy!